sequenceDiagram
    participant Browser as Browser User
    participant SAClient as Service Account Client
    participant AuthProxy as kube-auth-proxy<br/>4180/TCP HTTP
    participant RBACProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant OIDC as OIDC Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OSAuth as OpenShift OAuth<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant OSUser as OpenShift User API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Upstream as Upstream App<br/>HTTP/HTTPS

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 1: OIDC Browser Authentication (auth mode)

    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/start
    AuthProxy->>OIDC: 302 Redirect to authorize endpoint<br/>OAuth2 client_id (query)
    Browser->>OIDC: Login page (user credentials)
    OIDC->>Browser: 302 Redirect to /oauth2/callback<br/>authorization code
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/callback<br/>CSRF cookie + auth code
    AuthProxy->>OIDC: POST token endpoint<br/>client credentials + auth code
    OIDC-->>AuthProxy: Access token + ID token
    AuthProxy-->>Browser: Set-Cookie: encrypted session (AES-CFB)
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /* with session cookie
    AuthProxy->>Upstream: Proxied request<br/>GAP-Auth header

    Note over Browser,Upstream: Flow 2: OpenShift OAuth Authentication (auth mode)

    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/start
    AuthProxy->>OSAuth: GET /.well-known/oauth-authorization-server
    OSAuth-->>AuthProxy: OAuth metadata (URLs)
    AuthProxy->>Browser: 302 Redirect to OpenShift authorize
    Browser->>OSAuth: Login page (user credentials)
    OSAuth->>Browser: 302 Redirect to /oauth2/callback<br/>authorization code
    Browser->>AuthProxy: GET /oauth2/callback<br/>CSRF cookie + auth code
    AuthProxy->>OSAuth: POST token endpoint<br/>client_id + client_secret + code
    OSAuth-->>AuthProxy: Access token
    AuthProxy->>OSUser: GET /apis/user.openshift.io/v1/users/~<br/>Bearer access token
    OSUser-->>AuthProxy: User info (name, email, groups)
    AuthProxy-->>Browser: Set-Cookie: encrypted session

    Note over SAClient,Upstream: Flow 3: K8s RBAC Authorization (rbac mode)

    SAClient->>RBACProxy: Request with Bearer token<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: POST TokenReview<br/>Service account token
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: TokenReview result (user identity)
    RBACProxy->>K8sAPI: POST SubjectAccessReview<br/>ResourceAttributes
    K8sAPI-->>RBACProxy: SubjectAccessReview result (allowed/denied)
    RBACProxy->>Upstream: Proxied request<br/>x-remote-user, x-remote-groups

    Note over SAClient,Upstream: Flow 4: K8s SA Token Authentication (auth mode)

    SAClient->>AuthProxy: Request with Bearer SA token<br/>4180/TCP HTTP
    AuthProxy->>K8sAPI: POST TokenReview<br/>Service account token
    K8sAPI-->>AuthProxy: TokenReview result (SA identity)
    AuthProxy->>Upstream: Proxied request<br/>GAP-Auth header (SA username)
